-- Egypt Obtains $392 Million Japan Loan to Fund Metro Expansion
-- B y   A b d e l   L a t i f   W a h b a   a n d   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2012-03-19T11:21:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/egypt-obtains-392-million-japan-loan-to-fund-metro-expansion.html
Egypt  signed an agreement today on
a $392 million loan from  Japan  to finance the first phase of a
fourth metro line, according to a statement from the ministerial
council.  The funding is the first instalment of a $1.28 billion
Japanese loan that will be repaid over 30 years after a grace
period of 10 years, according to a statement from the office of
Fayza Aboulnaga, Egyptâ€™s minister of planning and international
cooperation.  The new metro line will connect the City of 6 October with
central Cairo and with tourist attractions such as the Pyramids
of Giza. It will have capacity for 500,000 passengers a day when
completed, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
